<br>
Mature and responsible are matters of opinion.  Suffice it to say I think every president we've ever had fits those qualities, even the ones I don't like.<br>
<br>
As far as appointed, he won in the electoral college.  There is a reason it's set up like that.  It was negotiated by the founding fathers to protect the rights of less populous states by increasing their representation compared to the more populous states.  The division in support between Gore and Bush was largely coastal/interior or urban/rural.  Bush won in a lot of smaller, less populated states and hence the electoral college and the way it was designed to increase representation of less populous states allowed him to win the election while losing the popular vote.<br>
<br>
