The Constitution doesn't say that the man who is elected president is the one who won the most votes.  It says it's the man who won the most electoral votes.  The Constitution was followed to the letter, and Bush won.  What part of the Consitution are you suggesting was not followed?  The Supreme Court ended a recount process that legally should have ended before it got to them.  The Florida Supreme Court made a partisan decision because it's a highly liberal court.  Even the chief justice of the Florida Supreme Court (a lifelong democrat) said in his dissenting opinion that the court had trampled the constitution of Florida for political reasons.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>bush uses &quot;some&quot; of the very ideas he talked about during the debates. except that he doesn't understand them and he is guided by the corporations that own him.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
